{
  "texts": [
    "The joint angle limits for each of the robot's six joints, provided to us by our industry partner, are defined as follows:• Joint 1: [-2.9671, 2.9671] radians • Joint 2: [-1.7453, 2.3562] radians • Joint 3: [-2.0769, 2.8972] radians • Joint 4: [-3.3161, 3.3161] radians • Joint 5: [-2.0944, 2.0944] radians • Joint 6: [-6.2832, 6.2832] radiansThese limits ensure that each joint operates within a safe and functional range, avoiding positions that could cause mechanical interference or exceed the robot's design specifications.",
    "Operators• Mutation: In the mutation phase, each number within the set of six undergoes mutation with an equal probability.",
    "If a number is going to be changed, a number within the possible range is generated.",
    "Accordingly, the new generated chromosome would be valid.• Crossover: For the crossover, two parents are selected.",
    "Each parent is chosen by tournament selection."
  ]
}